parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive vibration in the front end suspension can cause premature wear of the tires, leading to reduced traction and increased risk of accidents. Additionally, the vibration can cause damage to other components, such as the hood, spring hanger, steering arm, and bushings, which can lead to further safety issues.
symptoms: Excessive vibration in the front end
premature wear of the tires (especially on the left side)
and noise from the front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of the steer tires can lead to reduced traction and increased risk of accidents, especially when combined with other front end suspension issues.
symptoms: Premature wear of the steer tires

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the king pins and bushings can cause the front end suspension to malfunction, leading to vibration, premature tire wear, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: and difficulty keeping the tires aligned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the rear suspension bolts and lower shock mounts can cause the rear suspension to malfunction, leading to vibration, premature tire wear, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: and vibration in the rear end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature tire wear and failure can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and roadside hazards, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud noise coming from the right front of the vehicle
and wear on tire rod ends

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Suspension and Steering Component Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of front suspension and steering components can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and roadside hazards, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: and frequent replacements of these components.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Door and Window Weather Sealing Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door and window weather sealing can cause water and air to enter the cabin, leading to discomfort, distraction, and potentially affecting the driver's visibility, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Water and snow enter the cabin through the top of the door
windows flex or come off their tracks
water accumulates on the floor or seats.
